section.section:
For the calendar year in which an employee begins employment, the employee is entitled only to the following personal leave with pay:
6 days, not to exceed 48 hours, if employment begins on or after January 1 and on or before the last day in February;
5 days, not to exceed 40 hours, if employment begins on or after March 1 and on or before April 30;
4 days, not to exceed 32 hours, if employment begins on or after May 1 and on or before June 30; or
3 days, not to exceed 24 hours, if employment begins on or after July 1.
